# Bead browserplex-7p0.2 — DOCS

**No shipped user-facing docs change in this bead.** Rationale:

- The daemon has no user-facing entry point yet — it's launched internally (`node
  dist/daemon/server.js`) and will be fronted by the `bp` CLI (bead .3) with auto-spawn, and given
  explicit `bp serve|status|stop` controls in bead .5. There is nothing for a user to invoke or
  configure from this bead alone.
- The MCP server's public surface is unchanged.
- README/CHANGELOG coverage of the daemon + `bp` CLI is scoped to **bead .7 (Docs + packaging)**,
  once the user-facing commands exist.

The IPC wire protocol and daemon design are documented in
`docs/plans/process/browserplex-7p0.2-PLAN.md` (internal design, not shipped docs).
